RACE.RACE_TEXT: CTM Princess S. CENTURY MILE RACE 1 350 Y Dirt CR: 79. Stakes Purse 21800. A STAKE FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD QUARTER HORSE FILLIES & MARES. A payment of $200.00 is required at time of entry. Preference guides can be found in the AQHRA Stakes Book. Weight: Three-Year-Olds 124 lbs. Older: 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JESSAPRIMADONNA away well, dug in late under a hand ride and won the bob. O SEEYALATER showed the way and was bested late. NAUGHTEE OR NICE weakened late stretch. DECIDER CARTEL QUEEN broke outward into FIRELICIOUS and SCARLETTS CARTEL, and flattened late. TULSA TIMBER broke inward into SCARLETTS CARTEL, and offered a mild late bid. SHE WEARS THE PANTZ lacked a clear path early, and rallied late. KARI L CARTEL raced evenly. SCARLETTS CARTEL squeezed out away from the gate and trailed. FIRELICIOUS bumped sideways leaving the gate, and was unable to recover ground. STEWARDS INQUIRY- The Board of Stewards conducted an inquiry into the start of the race. After review, DECIDER CARTEL QUEEN was disqualified and placed eighth for interference to FIRELICIOUS and SCARLETTS CARTEL. TULSA TIMBER was disqualified and placed ninth for interference to FIRELICIOUS and SCARLETTS CARTEL.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Tulsa Timber
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, bumped, mild late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Jessaprimadonna
ENTRY.COMMENT: away well, dug in, won bob

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 13500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $ 15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESTIFRAAD assumed the lead in the sixth path, drew away nearing the quarter pole, was kept to task through the stretch, rider peered under his arm and was geared down. MOHAMAD tracked inside through the backstretch, chased the leader through the stretch but was no match and held for the place. ESCROW STYLE raced wide through the backstretch, gained closer order outside in the final turn, and closed well. PULL THE PIN stalked from the three path, was brushed leaving the backstretch, and faded gradually. LIGHTENING ANNA brushed PULL THE PIN leaving the backstretch while in close quarters, and lacked a bid. MAKE'N TRACKS never reached contention.

ENTRY.NAME: Pull the Pin
ENTRY.OWNER: Elliott, Madeleine, Langlois, Antoine, Oxley, Sandy and Walper, Deanna

ENTRY.NAME: Estifraad
ENTRY.OWNER: Tornado Racing and Frey Racing Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 12500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Lesser Claiming Races For $6,000 (AB $8,000) Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility). AB Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ADDYDIDIT was reserved off the early pacesetters, dropped back in the far turn, was asked to quicken nearing the quarter pole, drove between rivals capturing the lead, and was kept to task under a strong hand ride. COUNT ON IT chased four to five wide, rallied five wide at the head of the stretch, and was outkicked. TAKE CHARGE GWEN saved ground inside, moved up alongside LOAD ABROAD to challenge the lead after the three-sixteenth pole, and weakened in the stretch. CHATTY GAL vied outside for the early lead, settled in striking distance leaving the backstretch, raced in close quarters entering the stretch, and finished evenly. LOAD ABROAD showed the way through the backstretch under a stronghold, was under attack entering the stretch and yielded. WHEELSUPINTHIRTY chased wide and tired early. TRAINER OBJECTION- An objection lodged by the trainer of TAKE CHARGE GWEN against the rider of ADDYDIDIT alleging interference at the top of the stretch was not allowed.

ENTRY.NAME: Take Charge Gwen
ENTRY.OWNER: Profect Jay Freeman Carrie Robertson Jerri R and Hardy Lesley

ENTRY.NAME: Addydidit
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, dropped back, drove between, driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 19000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING $12,000 WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AMUSING WAY broke alertly then vied outside of NORTHERN DREAMIN for the early lead, sat just off the pace leaving the backstretch, overtook the lead willingly nearing the quarter pole, responded to a looming threat from DOUSEAWHATISEA, and stayed clear under light handling. ALL RUN lacked a clear path leaving, trailed the field, and closed determinedly getting up just in time for place honors. DOUSEAWHATISEA broke awkwardly, chased three to four wide, loomed at the head of the stretch then drifted in, was no match for the winner, and was run down late. PADDYS ROCKET chased in the second flight from the three path, and closed late. MIDNITE CHILL tracked outside, roused at the three-sixteenth marker, and came up empty for the drive. NORTHERN DREAMIN vied for the early lead, gained the advantage in the far turn, and faltered in the stretch.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 10000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Lesser Claiming Races Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $5,000 .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG AL'S VISION saved ground early, circled the field in the final turn, rallied outside, dug in the final yards and prevailed. FROBISHER BAY trailed the field early, drove inside nearing the stretch, rallied determinedly from the rail, and was out finished. PERDITION brushed away, chased early, lost path just after the three-sixteenth pole, angled out sharply, came under steady urging from the four path, and missed. ONEFINEDAY assumed the lead, angled to the two path when leaving the backstretch, was showing signs of tiring and then flattened out. DREADNAUGHT hurried inside, was never far back and lacked the kick that was needed. LET THE BOY SING hustled away, settled in the four path in striking range, came under encouragement at the head of the lane, and was unable to make much of an impact through the stretch. REDNECK REMARK saved ground, and passed tiring rival. YORKTOWN stalked from the rail, and gave way.

ENTRY.COMMENT: hurried inside, in range, lacked kick

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BORKAN contested the pace inside of COMMON KNOWLEDGE, drew clear nearing the quarter pole, and opened up to win easily. SMARTY RIVER PANTS lacked running room in the far turn, bid inside nearing the stretch, and held firm for second. SCHOCHOH sat in range while five wide, fanned four wide in the far turn, was roused at the quarter pole then went in pursuit of the leader, was no match in the stretch and was outkicked for place. SHARP DRESSED BEAU raced from the back of the pack, circled into the lane, and closed gradually. COMMON KNOWLEDGE showed early speed but was outsprinted to the turn, and lacked a response when called upon. HARD TO COME HOME attended the pace from the four path, was unable to keep pace with the field and wilted.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $17,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $22,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BON PRIX contested the pace racing four wide into the far turn, gained a short advantage entering the lane, was unchallenged in the stretch and was ridden out. BACKSTREET BOBBY set the early pace inside, was overtaken in the far turn, came under heaving urging from along the rail, was no match for the winner and finished well for second. RAILWAY brushed ARGENTINA CRIES in the backstretch, hustled outside in the final turn, and closed gradually under steady urging. LINCHPIN STORM sat in range while wide, rallied outside of RAILWAY through the stretch, and improved late. ARGENTINA CRIES (IRE) was brushed in the backstretch, fanned three-wide in the far turn, chased through the stretch, and gave way. TUCKER TIME chased inside, and rallied belatedly. ABOVE AND BEYOND attended the early pace, and came up empty in the drive. IMPACTO showed little.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $31,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKTILLYOUDROP saved ground in the second flight while four wide through the backstretch, took closer order in the final turn, grabbed the lead shortly afterward, and drew clear. WAR GIANT reserved well off the pace, drove five to six wide at the head of the lane, rallied inside of FATHER O'FLAHERTY and held on for second. FATHER O'FLAHERTY raced from the back of the field, advanced quickly while wide through the final turn, match strides through the stretch outside of WAR GIANT but was unable to get by. ZICATELA dueled outside SMART PLAY for the lead, failed to respond to the challenge from ROCKTILLYOUDROP at the head of the lane, and weakened. WALKTHELINE saved to no avail. SMART PLAY disputed the early lead inside of ZICATELA, was unable to move on with rival, and yielded.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 9 6F Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VANTASTICCANAVERAL contested the pace outside, responded to challengers into the stretch, rival took a slim lead but refused to go down without a fight, dug in gamely in the final strides to narrowly prevail. H K RAPPER settled into a stalking position from along the rail, lacked running room nearing the three-sixteenth pole, saw running room inside then drove up grabbing the lead, matched strides in the final sixteenth inside of VANTASTICCANAVERAL, and was nailed before the wire. BARAK stalked the early pacesetters, drove five wide at the top of the lane, rallied mildly through the stretch, and was along late for the show. ADIOS Y GRACIAS opted to settle well off the pace, swung outside in the final turn, and closed gradually. REAL JUSTICE lodged a rail bid nearing the quarter pole, and flattened in the drive. FROSTEDBIRD brushed leaving, contested the early pace inside of VANTASTICCANAVERAL, was unable to move on with rival near the three-sixteenth marker, and gave way. KAPTAIN KOWBOY away well but lacked the early speed needed, circled into the lane, and failed to threaten. NIGHTFALL chased wide and offered a late mild bid. CAROSWAY brushed rival leaving, chased five wide, and was unable to keep pace with his field. RAUSTY TREASURE never reached contention.
